Axis Bank Said to Hold Meetings With Bond Investors This Week

-- B y   A n u r a g   J o s h i
-- 
2011-05-12T06:07:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-12/axis-bank-said-to-hold-meetings-with-bond-investors-this-week.html
Axis Bank Ltd. (AXSB) , India’s third-biggest
private lender, held meetings this week to update bond investors
on recent corporate developments, according to a person familiar
with the matter.  The Mumbai-based lender met with investors in  Hong Kong ,
Los Angeles, New York and Singapore, the person said, asking not
to be identified as the details are private. Axis is also
scheduled to meet with investors in London, the person said.  The bank doesn’t have any immediate plans to sell bonds,
said the person.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anurag Joshi in Mumbai 
